post_text: The Centennial Board of Education is pleased to announce the hiring of Dr. Virginia Moon as Interim Superintendent of Centennial Public School. Dr. Moon‚Äôs experience is extensive, including 11 years as Ralston Superintendent, as well as Interim Superintendent positions at Broken Bow Public Schools, Omaha Public Schools, Kearney Public Schools, & most recently at Auburn Public Schools. The Board of Education looks forward to working with Dr. Moon & asks all Centennial families to welcome her to our school district. Dr. Moon‚Äôs contract begins immediately and expires on June 30, 2021. The Board of Education will conduct an extensive & thorough search for a permanent Superintendent at the appropriate time & will update the public during the fall about that process. Jason Richters, Centennial Board of Education President.

Dr. Moon‚Äôs experience is extensive, including 11 years as Ralston Superintendent, as well as Interim Superintendent positions at Broken Bow Public Schools, Omaha Public Schools, Kearney Public Schools, & most recently at Auburn Public Schools. post_text: Like many of the schools in the area & state, Centennial is working to determine what the start of the school year will look like. Our hope & goal is that we will be starting school on time with students in the building. The administration will be working with our local health department to determine how we can safely start school & will be meeting to finalize plans at the end of July. Things are constantly changing & we are trying to stay up to date with the latest information. We will share more information with you no later than Aug. 3rd. Thank you for your patience & understanding.

Our hope & goal is that we will be starting school on time with students in the building. The administration will be working with our local health department to determine how we can safely start school & will be meeting to finalize plans at the end of July. Things are constantly changing & we are trying to stay up to date with the latest information. We will share more information with you no later than Aug. 3rd. Thank you for your patience & understanding.

post_text:
With all of the changes we are experiencing with canceled events and changes in our communities, YNT has decided to publish a Super Senior magazine featuring the graduates of all area high schools that we cover, including Nebraska Lutheran. Included schools are: Hampton, Heartland, Osceola, McCool, Nebraska Lutheran, High Plains, Centennial, Cross County, Exeter-Milligan, Fillmore Central and York. The magazine will be a full color, glossy magazine (7.75‚Äù x 9.75‚Äù) which we hope will be a keepsake for students, families, community members and more. The senior class members from each school will also receive a complimentary copy.
Advertising sponsorship space is also available in the magazine. I have attached a sales flyer with the ad sizes and prices. Our deadline to reserve ad space is April 22nd. Please let me know if you have any questions.

PAULA MILLER
Advertising & Marketing Consultant
paula.miller@yorknewstimes.com

BOX TOPS! Hello all. During this crazy time, one thing has continued, we still buy groceries! Collection of Box Tops has changed quite a bit over the last year or so. The majority of them are now counted electronically with an app. You load the app on your phone at BTFE.com and take a picture of your receipt within 14 days. The app explains the process quite well. You can select Centennial School as your school and the .10 per box top will go into our box top account at Centennial! It‚Äôs that simple. I have tried this out over the last couple weeks and it works fairly well. There were a few glitches, but I was able to work through them. Long receipts prove to be quite tricky. If there are grandmas of others out there that want to contribute to more than one school, you are able to donate to more than one school. If you come across a few of the old style clip Box Tops, you can still send those to the school. We would appreciate your help in continuing the collection of Box Tops electronically! Thank you!
BTFE.com
